fields.name: MODE
fields.desc: This bits decides which one operation mode will be used. 3'd0: AES-EN-128, 3'd1: AES-EN-192, 3'd2: AES-EN-256, 3'd4: AES-DE-128, 3'd5: AES-DE-192, 3'd6: AES-DE-256.

fields.name: ENDIAN
fields.desc: endian. [1:0] key endian, [3:2] text_in endian or in_stream endian,  [5:4] text_out endian or out_stream endian

fields.name: TRIGGER
fields.desc: Set this bit to start AES calculation.

fields.name: STATE
fields.desc: Those bits shows AES status. For typical AES, 0: idle, 1: busy. For DMA-AES, 0: idle, 1: busy, 2: calculation_done.

1611169872.name: IV_MEM[%s]
1611169872.desc: The memory that stores initialization vector

1611169888.name: H_MEM[%s]
1611169888.desc: The memory that stores GCM hash subkey

fields.name: DMA_ENABLE
fields.desc: 1'b0: typical AES working mode, 1'b1: DMA-AES working mode.

fields.name: BLOCK_MODE
fields.desc: Those bits decides which block mode will be used. 0x0: ECB, 0x1: CBC, 0x2: OFB, 0x3: CTR, 0x4: CFB-8, 0x5: CFB-128, 0x6: GCM, 0x7: reserved.

fields.name: BLOCK_NUM
fields.desc: Those bits stores the number of Plaintext/ciphertext block.

fields.name: INC_SEL
fields.desc: This bit decides the standard incrementing function. 0: INC32. 1: INC128.

1611169952.name: AAD_BLOCK_NUM
1611169952.desc: Additional Authential Data block number register

fields.name: AAD_BLOCK_NUM
fields.desc: Those bits stores the number of AAD block.

fields.name: REMAINDER_BIT_NUM
fields.desc: Those bits stores the number of remainder bit.

fields.name: CONTINUE
fields.desc: Set this bit to continue GCM operation.

fields.name: INT_CLEAR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear the AES interrupt.

fields.name: INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable interrupt that occurs when DMA-AES calculation is done.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: This bits stores the version information of AES.

fields.name: DMA_EXIT
fields.desc: Set this register to leave calculation done stage. Recommend to use it after software finishes reading DMA's output buffer.

For UHCI0 the raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received and no data error is detected for Rx channel 0.

fields.name: IN_DSCR_EMPTY

fields.name: INFIFO_UDF
fields.desc: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 1 fifo of Rx channel 0 is underflow.

Configures the low level width of the SCL
Clock

fields.desc: This register is used to configure for how long SCL remains low in master mode, in I2C module clock cycles.

fields.name: SDA_FORCE_OUT
fields.desc: 1: direct output, 0: open drain output.

fields.name: SCL_FORCE_OUT
fields.desc: 1: direct output, 0: open drain output.

fields.name: SAMPLE_SCL_LEVEL
fields.desc:
This register is used to select the sample mode.
1: sample SDA data on the SCL low level.
0: sample SDA data on the SCL high level.

fields.name: RX_FULL_ACK_LEVEL
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the ACK value that need to sent by master when the rx_fifo_cnt has reached the threshold.

fields.name: MS_MODE
fields.desc:
Set this bit to configure the module as an I2C Master. Clear this bit to configure the
module as an I2C Slave.

fields.name: TRANS_START
fields.desc: Set this bit to start sending the data in txfifo.

fields.name: TX_LSB_FIRST
fields.desc:
This bit is used to control the sending mode for data needing to be sent. 
1: send data from the least significant bit,
0: send data from the most significant bit.

fields.name: RX_LSB_FIRST
fields.desc:
This bit is used to control the storage mode for received data.
1: receive data from the least significant bit,
0: receive data from the most significant bit.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: ARBITRATION_EN
fields.desc: This is the enable bit for arbitration_lost.

fields.name: FSM_RST
fields.desc: This register is used to reset the scl FMS.

fields.name: CONF_UPGATE
fields.desc: synchronization bit

fields.name: SLV_TX_AUTO_START_EN
fields.desc: This is the enable bit for slave to send data automatically

fields.name: ADDR_10BIT_RW_CHECK_EN
fields.desc: This is the enable bit to check if the r/w bit of 10bit addressing consists with I2C protocol

fields.name: ADDR_BROADCASTING_EN
fields.desc: This is the enable bit to support the 7bit general call function.

fields.name: RESP_REC
fields.desc: The received ACK value in master mode or slave mode. 0: ACK, 1: NACK.

fields.name: SLAVE_RW
fields.desc: When in slave mode, 1: master reads from slave, 0: master writes to slave.

fields.name: ARB_LOST
fields.desc: When the I2C controller loses control of SCL line, this register changes to 1.

fields.name: BUS_BUSY
fields.desc: 1: the I2C bus is busy transferring data, 0: the I2C bus is in idle state.

fields.name: SLAVE_ADDRESSED
fields.desc:
When configured as an I2C Slave, and the address sent by the master is
equal to the address of the slave, then this bit will be of high level.

fields.name: RXFIFO_CNT
fields.desc: This field represents the amount of data needed to be sent.

fields.name: STRETCH_CAUSE
fields.desc: The cause of stretching SCL low in slave mode. 0:  stretching SCL low at the beginning of I2C read data state. 1: stretching SCL low when I2C Tx FIFO is empty in slave mode. 2: stretching SCL low when I2C Rx FIFO is full in slave mode.

fields.name: TXFIFO_CNT
fields.desc: This field stores the amount of received data in RAM.

fields.name: SCL_MAIN_STATE_LAST
fields.desc:
This field indicates the states of the I2C module state machine. 
0: Idle, 1: Address shift, 2: ACK address, 3: Rx data, 4: Tx data, 5: Send ACK, 6: Wait ACK

fields.name: SCL_STATE_LAST
fields.desc:
This field indicates the states of the state machine used to produce SCL.
0: Idle, 1: Start, 2: Negative edge, 3: Low, 4: Positive edge, 5: High, 6: Stop

1610629168.name: SDA_HOLD
1610629168.desc: Configures the hold time after a negative SCL edge.

fields.name: TIME
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the time to hold the data after the negative
edge of SCL, in I2C module clock cycles.

1610629172.name: SDA_SAMPLE
1610629172.desc: Configures the sample time after a positive SCL edge.

fields.name: TIME
fields.desc: This register is used to configure for how long SDA is sampled, in I2C module clock cycles.

1610629176.name: SCL_HIGH_PERIOD
1610629176.desc: Configures the high level width of SCL

fields.desc: This register is used to configure for how long SCL remains high in master mode, in I2C module clock cycles.

fields.name: SCL_WAIT_HIGH_PERIOD
fields.desc: This register is used to configure for the SCL_FSM's waiting period for SCL high level in master mode, in I2C module clock cycles.

1610629184.name: SCL_START_HOLD
1610629184.desc: Configures the delay between the SDA and SCL negative edge for a start condition

fields.name: TIME
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the time between the negative edge
of SDA and the negative edge of SCL for a START condition, in I2C module clock cycles.

1610629188.name: SCL_RSTART_SETUP
1610629188.desc:
Configures the delay between the positive
edge of SCL and the negative edge of SDA

fields.name: TIME
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the time between the positive
edge of SCL and the negative edge of SDA for a RESTART condition, in I2C module clock cycles.

1610629192.name: SCL_STOP_HOLD
1610629192.desc:
Configures the delay after the SCL clock
edge for a stop condition

fields.name: TIME
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the delay after the STOP condition,
in I2C module clock cycles.

1610629196.name: SCL_STOP_SETUP
1610629196.desc:
Configures the delay between the SDA and
SCL positive edge for a stop condition

fields.name: TIME
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the time between the positive edge
of SCL and the positive edge of SDA, in I2C module clock cycles.

1610629200.name: FILTER_CFG
1610629200.desc: SCL and SDA filter configuration register

fields.name: SCL_FILTER_THRES
fields.desc:
When a pulse on the SCL input has smaller width than this register value
in I2C module clock cycles, the I2C controller will ignore that pulse.

fields.name: SDA_FILTER_THRES
fields.desc:
When a pulse on the SDA input has smaller width than this register value
in I2C module clock cycles, the I2C controller will ignore that pulse.

fields.name: SCL_FILTER_EN
fields.desc: This is the filter enable bit for SCL.

fields.name: SDA_FILTER_EN
fields.desc: This is the filter enable bit for SDA.

fields.name: SCLK_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: the integral part of the fractional divisor for i2c module

fields.name: SCLK_DIV_A
fields.desc: the numerator of the fractional part of the fractional divisor for i2c module

fields.name: SCLK_DIV_B
fields.desc: the denominator of the fractional part of the fractional divisor for i2c module

fields.name: SCLK_SEL
fields.desc: The clock selection for i2c module:0-XTAL,1-CLK_8MHz.

fields.name: SCLK_ACTIVE
fields.desc: The clock switch for i2c module

fields.name: COMMAND
fields.desc:
This is the content of command 0. It consists of three parts: 
op_code is the command, 0: RSTART, 1: WRITE, 2: READ, 3: STOP, 4: END.
Byte_num represents the number of bytes that need to be sent or received.
ack_check_en, ack_exp and ack are used to control the ACK bit. See I2C cmd structure for more
Information.

fields.name: COMMAND_DONE
fields.desc:
When command 0 is done in I2C Master mode, this bit changes to high
level.

fields.name: SCL_ST_TO_I2C
fields.desc: The threshold value of SCL_FSM state unchanged period. It should be o more than 23

1610629244.name: SCL_MAIN_ST_TIME_OUT
1610629244.desc: SCL main status time out register

fields.name: SCL_MAIN_ST_TO_I2C
fields.desc: The threshold value of SCL_MAIN_FSM state unchanged period.nIt should be o more than 23

fields.name: SCL_RST_SLV_EN
fields.desc: When I2C master is IDLE, set this bit to send out SCL pulses. The number of pulses equals to reg_scl_rst_slv_num[4:0].

fields.name: SCL_RST_SLV_NUM
fields.desc: Configure the pulses of SCL generated in I2C master mode. Valid when reg_scl_rst_slv_en is 1.

fields.name: SCL_PD_EN
fields.desc: The power down enable bit for the I2C output SCL line. 1: Power down. 0: Not power down. Set reg_scl_force_out and reg_scl_pd_en to 1 to stretch SCL low.

fields.name: SDA_PD_EN
fields.desc: The power down enable bit for the I2C output SDA line. 1: Power down. 0: Not power down. Set reg_sda_force_out and reg_sda_pd_en to 1 to stretch SDA low.

1610629252.name: SCL_STRETCH_CONF
1610629252.desc: Set SCL stretch of I2C slave

fields.name: STRETCH_PROTECT_NUM
fields.desc: Configure the period of I2C slave stretching SCL line.

fields.name: SLAVE_SCL_STRETCH_EN
fields.desc: The enable bit for slave SCL stretch function. 1: Enable. 0: Disable. The SCL output line will be stretched low when reg_slave_scl_stretch_en is 1 and stretch event happens. The stretch cause can be seen in reg_stretch_cause.

fields.name: SLAVE_SCL_STRETCH_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear the I2C slave SCL stretch function.

fields.name: SLAVE_BYTE_ACK_CTL_EN
fields.desc: The enable bit for slave to control ACK level function.

fields.name: SLAVE_BYTE_ACK_LVL
fields.desc: Set the ACK level when slave controlling ACK level function enables.

fields.name: DATE

fields.name: RX_START
fields.desc: Set this bit to start receiving data

fields.name: RX_SLAVE_MOD

fields.desc: 0  : I2S Rx only stop when reg_rx_start is cleared.   1: Stop when reg_rx_start is 0 or in_suc_eof is 1.   2:  Stop I2S RX when reg_rx_start is 0 or RX FIFO is full.

fields.name: RX_MONO
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable receiver  in mono mode

fields.name: RX_BIG_ENDIAN
fields.desc: I2S Rx byte endian, 1: low addr value to high addr. 0: low addr with low addr value.

fields.name: RX_UPDATE
fields.desc: Set 1 to update I2S RX registers from APB clock domain to I2S RX clock domain. This bit will be cleared by hardware after update register done.

fields.name: RX_MONO_FST_VLD
fields.desc: 1: The first channel data value is valid in I2S RX mono mode.   0: The second channel data value is valid in I2S RX mono mode.

fields.name: RX_PCM_CONF
fields.desc: I2S RX compress/decompress configuration bit. & 0 (atol): A-Law decompress, 1 (ltoa) : A-Law compress, 2 (utol) : u-Law decompress, 3 (ltou) : u-Law compress. &

fields.name: RX_PCM_BYPASS
fields.desc: Set this bit to bypass Compress/Decompress module for received data.

fields.name: RX_MSB_SHIFT
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable receiver in Phillips standard mode

fields.name: RX_LEFT_ALIGN
fields.desc: 1: I2S RX left alignment mode. 0: I2S RX right alignment mode.

fields.name: RX_24_FILL_EN
fields.desc: 1: store 24 channel bits to 32 bits. 0:store 24 channel bits to 24 bits.

fields.name: RX_WS_IDLE_POL
fields.desc: 0: WS should be 0 when receiving left channel data, and WS is 1in right channel.  1: WS should be 1 when receiving left channel data, and WS is 0in right channel.

fields.name: RX_BIT_ORDER
fields.desc: I2S Rx bit endian. 1:small endian, the LSB is received first. 0:big endian, the MSB is received first.

fields.name: RX_TDM_EN
fields.desc: 1: Enable I2S TDM Rx mode . 0: Disable.

fields.name: RX_PDM_EN
fields.desc: 1: Enable I2S PDM Rx mode . 0: Disable.

fields.name: RX_BCK_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: Bit clock configuration bits in receiver mode.

fields.desc: Set this bit to reset transmitter

fields.desc: Set this bit to reset Tx AFIFO

fields.name: TX_START
fields.desc: Set this bit to start transmitting data

fields.name: TX_SLAVE_MOD
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable slave transmitter mode

fields.desc: Set this bit to stop disable output BCK signal and WS signal when tx FIFO is emtpy

fields.desc: 1: The value of Left channel data is equal to the value of right channel data in I2S TX mono mode or TDM channel select mode. 0: The invalid channel data is reg_i2s_single_data in I2S TX mono mode or TDM channel select mode.

fields.name: TX_MONO
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable transmitter in mono mode

fields.name: TX_BIG_ENDIAN
fields.desc: I2S Tx byte endian, 1: low addr value to high addr.  0: low addr with low addr value.

fields.name: TX_PCM_BYPASS
fields.desc: Set this bit to bypass  Compress/Decompress module for transmitted data.

fields.name: TX_MSB_SHIFT
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable transmitter in Phillips standard mode

fields.name: TX_BCK_NO_DLY
fields.desc: 1: BCK is not delayed to generate pos/neg edge in master mode. 0: BCK is delayed to generate pos/neg edge in master mode.

fields.name: TX_LEFT_ALIGN
fields.desc: 1: I2S TX left alignment mode. 0: I2S TX right alignment mode.

fields.name: TX_24_FILL_EN
fields.desc: 1: Sent 32 bits in 24 channel bits mode. 0: Sent 24 bits in 24 channel bits mode

fields.name: TX_WS_IDLE_POL
fields.desc: 0: WS should be 0 when sending left channel data, and WS is 1in right channel.  1: WS should be 1 when sending left channel data, and WS is 0in right channel.

fields.name: TX_BIT_ORDER
fields.desc: I2S Tx bit endian. 1:small endian, the LSB is sent first. 0:big endian, the MSB is sent first.

fields.name: TX_TDM_EN
fields.desc: 1: Enable I2S TDM Tx mode . 0: Disable.

fields.name: TX_PDM_EN
fields.desc: 1: Enable I2S PDM Tx mode . 0: Disable.

fields.name: TX_BCK_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: Bit clock configuration bits in transmitter mode.

fields.name: TX_CHAN_MOD
fields.desc: I2S transmitter channel mode configuration bits.

fields.name: RX_TDM_WS_WIDTH
fields.desc: The width of rx_ws_out at idle level in TDM mode is (I2S_RX_TDM_WS_WIDTH[8:0] +1) * T_bck

fields.desc: Set the bits to configure the valid data bit length of I2S receiver channel. 7: all the valid channel data is in 8-bit-mode. 15: all the valid channel data is in 16-bit-mode. 23: all the valid channel data is in 24-bit-mode. 31:all the valid channel data is in 32-bit-mode.

fields.name: RX_HALF_SAMPLE_BITS
fields.desc: I2S Rx half sample bits -1.

fields.name: RX_TDM_CHAN_BITS
fields.desc: The Rx bit number for each channel minus 1in TDM mode.

fields.name: TX_TDM_WS_WIDTH
fields.desc: The width of tx_ws_out at idle level in TDM mode is (I2S_TX_TDM_WS_WIDTH[8:0] +1) * T_bck

fields.name: TX_BITS_MOD
fields.desc: Set the bits to configure the valid data bit length of I2S transmitter channel. 7: all the valid channel data is in 8-bit-mode. 15: all the valid channel data is in 16-bit-mode. 23: all the valid channel data is in 24-bit-mode. 31:all the valid channel data is in 32-bit-mode.

fields.name: MCLK_SEL
fields.desc: 0: UseI2S Tx module clock as I2S_MCLK_OUT.  1: UseI2S Rx module clock as I2S_MCLK_OUT.

fields.name: TX_CLKM_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: Integral I2S TX clock divider value. f_I2S_CLK = f_I2S_CLK_S/(N+b/a). There will be (a-b) * n-div and b * (n+1)-div.  So the average combination will be:  for b <= a/2, z * [x * n-div + (n+1)-div] + y * n-div. For b > a/2, z * [n-div + x * (n+1)-div] + y * (n+1)-div.

fields.name: TX_CLK_ACTIVE
fields.desc: I2S Tx module clock enable signal.

fields.name: TX_CLK_SEL
fields.desc: Select I2S Tx module source clock. 0: XTAL clock. 1: APLL. 2: CLK160. 3: I2S_MCLK_in.

fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_Y is (a%b) . For b > a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_Y is (a%(a-b)).

fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_X is (a/b) - 1. For b > a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_X is (a/(a-b)) - 1.

fields.name: RX_CLKM_DIV_YN1
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_YN1 is 0 . For b > a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_YN1 is 1.

fields.name: TX_CLKM_DIV_X

1611202564.name: GPIO%s
1611202564.desc: IO MUX Configure Register for pad GPIO0

fields.name: MCU_OE
fields.desc: Output enable of the pad in sleep mode. 1: output enabled. 0: output disabled.

fields.name: SLP_SEL
fields.desc: Sleep mode selection of this pad. Set to 1 to put the pad in pad mode.

fields.name: MCU_WPD
fields.desc: Pull-down enable of the pad in sleep mode. 1: internal pull-down enabled. 0: internal pull-down disabled.

fields.name: MCU_WPU
fields.desc: Pull-up enable of the pad during sleep mode. 1: internal pull-up enabled. 0: internal pull-up disabled.

fields.name: MCU_IE
fields.desc: Input enable of the pad during sleep mode. 1: input enabled. 0: input disabled.

fields.name: MCU_DRV
fields.desc: Select the drive strength of the pad during sleep mode. 0: ~5 mA. 1: ~10mA. 2: ~20mA. 3: ~40mA.

fields.name: FUN_WPD
fields.desc: Pull-down enable of the pad. 1: internal pull-down enabled. 0: internal pull-down disabled.

fields.name: FUN_WPU
fields.desc: Pull-up enable of the pad. 1: internal pull-up enabled. 0: internal pull-up disabled.

fields.name: FUN_IE
fields.desc: Input enable of the pad. 1: input enabled. 0: input disabled.

fields.name: FUN_DRV
fields.desc: Select the drive strength of the pad. 0: ~5 mA. 1: ~10mA. 2: ~20mA. 3: ~40mA.

fields.name: MCU_SEL
fields.desc: Select IO MUX function for this signal. 0: Select Function 1. 1: Select Function 2. etc.

fields.name: FILTER_EN
fields.desc: Enable filter for pin input signals. 1: Filter enabled. 0: Filter disabled.

fields.name: HYS_EN
fields.desc: Software enables hysteresis function for the pad. 1: Hysteresis enabled. 0: Hysteresis disabled.

fields.name: HYS_SEL
fields.desc: Select enabling signals of the pad from software and efuse hardware. 1: Select enabling siganl from slftware. 0: Select enabling signal from efuse hardware.

1611202748.name: MODEM_DIAG_EN
1611202748.desc: GPIO MATRIX Configure Register for modem diag

fields.name: MODEM_DIAG_EN
fields.desc: bit i to enable modem_diag[i] into gpio matrix. 1:enable modem_diag[i] into gpio matrix. 0:enable other signals into gpio matrix

fields.name: REG_DATE
fields.desc: Version control register

fields.name: TIMER_SEL
fields.desc:
This field is used to select one of timers for channel %s.

0: select timer0, 1: select timer1, 2: select timer2, 3: select timer3

fields.name: SIG_OUT_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable signal output on channel %s.

fields.name: IDLE_LV
fields.desc: This bit is used to control the output value when channel %s is inactive (when LEDC_SIG_OUT_EN_CH%s is 0).

fields.name: PARA_UP
fields.desc: This bit is used to update LEDC_HPOINT_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_START_CH%s, LEDC_SIG_OUT_EN_CH%s, LEDC_TIMER_SEL_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_NUM_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_CYCLE_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_SCALE_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_INC_CH%s, and LEDC_OVF_CNT_EN_CH%s fields for channel %s, and will be automatically cleared by hardware.

fields.name: OVF_NUM
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the maximum times of overflow minus 1.

The LEDC_OVF_CNT_CH%s_INT interrupt will be triggered when channel %s overflows for (LEDC_OVF_NUM_CH%s + 1) times.

fields.name: OVF_CNT_EN
fields.desc: This bit is used to enable the ovf_cnt of channel %s.

fields.name: OVF_CNT_RESET
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset the ovf_cnt of channel %s.

fields.name: HPOINT
fields.desc: The output value changes to high when the selected timers has reached the value specified by this register.

fields.name: DUTY
fields.desc:
This register is used to change the output duty by controlling the Lpoint.

The output value turns to low when the selected timers has reached the Lpoint.

fields.name: DUTY_START
fields.desc: Other configured fields in LEDC_CH%s_CONF1_REG will start to take effect when this bit is set to 1.

fields.name: DUTY_CH_R
fields.desc: This register stores the current duty of output signal on channel %s.

fields.name: DUTY_RES
fields.desc: This register is used to control the range of the counter in timer %s.

fields.name: CLK_DIV
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the divisor for the divider in timer %s.

The least significant eight bits represent the fractional part.

fields.name: PAUSE
fields.desc: This bit is used to suspend the counter in timer %s.

fields.name: RST
fields.desc: This bit is used to reset timer %s. The counter will show 0 after reset.

fields.name: TICK_SEL
fields.desc:
This bit is used to select clock for timer %s. When this bit is set to 1 LEDC_APB_CLK_SEL[1:0] should be 1, otherwise the timer clock may be not accurate.

1'h0: SLOW_CLK 1'h1: REF_TICK

fields.name: PARA_UP
fields.desc: Set this bit to update LEDC_CLK_DIV_TIMER%s and LEDC_TIMER%s_DUTY_RES.

fields.name: TIMER_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the current counter value of timer %s.

fields.name: TIMER0_OVF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Triggered when the timer0 has reached its maximum counter value.

fields.name: TIMER1_OVF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Triggered when the timer1 has reached its maximum counter value.

fields.name: TIMER2_OVF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Triggered when the timer2 has reached its maximum counter value.

fields.name: TIMER3_OVF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Triggered when the timer3 has reached its maximum counter value.

fields.name: DUTY_CHNG_END_CH0_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Interrupt raw bit for channel 0. Triggered when the gradual change of duty has finished.

fields.name: DUTY_CHNG_END_CH1_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Interrupt raw bit for channel 1. Triggered when the gradual change of duty has finished.

fields.name: DUTY_CHNG_END_CH2_INT_RAW

fields.desc: Interrupt raw bit for channel 4. Triggered when the gradual change of duty has finished.

fields.name: DUTY_CHNG_END_CH5_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Interrupt raw bit for channel 5. Triggered when the gradual change of duty has finished.

fields.name: OVF_CNT_CH0_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Interrupt raw bit for channel 0. Triggered when the ovf_cnt has reached the value specified by LEDC_OVF_NUM_CH0.

fields.name: OVF_CNT_CH1_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Interrupt raw bit for channel 1. Triggered when the ovf_cnt has reached the value specified by LEDC_OVF_NUM_CH1.

fields.name: OVF_CNT_CH2_INT_RAW

fields.name: OVF_CNT_CH3_INT_RAW

fields.name: OVF_CNT_CH4_INT_RAW

fields.name: OVF_CNT_CH5_INT_RAW

fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt status bit for the LEDC_TIMER0_OVF_INT interrupt when LEDC_TIMER0_OVF_INT_ENA is set to 1.

fields.name: TIMER1_OVF_INT_ST

1610694660.name: TIMER0_CFG0
1610694660.desc: PWM timer0 period and update method configuration register.

fields.name: TIMER0_PRESCALE
fields.desc: period of PT0_clk = Period of PWM_clk * (PWM_TIMER0_PRESCALE + 1)

fields.name: TIMER0_PERIOD
fields.desc: period shadow register of PWM timer0

fields.name: TIMER0_PERIOD_UPMETHOD
fields.desc: Update method for active register of PWM timer0 period, 0: immediate, 1: TEZ, 2: sync, 3: TEZ | sync. TEZ here and below means timer equal zero event

1610694664.name: TIMER0_CFG1
1610694664.desc: PWM timer0 working mode and start/stop control configuration register.

fields.name: TIMER0_START
fields.desc: PWM timer0 start and stop control. 0: if PWM timer0 starts, then stops at TEZ, 1: if timer0 starts, then stops at TEP, 2: PWM timer0 starts and runs on, 3: timer0 starts and stops at the next TEZ, 4: timer0 starts and stops at the next TEP. TEP here and below means the event that happens when the timer equals to period

fields.name: TIMER0_MOD
fields.desc: PWM timer0 working mode, 0: freeze, 1: increase mode, 2: decrease mode, 3: up-down mode

1610694668.name: TIMER0_SYNC
1610694668.desc: PWM timer0 sync function configuration register.

fields.name: TIMER0_SYNCI_EN
fields.desc: When set, timer reloading with phase on sync input event is enabled.

fields.name: SW
fields.desc: Toggling this bit will trigger a software sync.

fields.name: TIMER0_SYNCO_SEL
fields.desc: PWM timer0 sync_out selection, 0: sync_in, 1: TEZ, 2: TEP, and sync out will always generate when toggling the reg_timer0_sync_sw bit

fields.name: TIMER0_PHASE
fields.desc: phase for timer reload on sync event

fields.name: TIMER0_PHASE_DIRECTION
fields.desc: Configure the PWM timer0's direction when timer0 mode is up-down mode: 0-increase,1-decrease

fields.name: TIMER0_VALUE
fields.desc: current PWM timer0 counter value

fields.name: TIMER0_DIRECTION
fields.desc: current PWM timer0 counter direction, 0: increment 1: decrement

1610694716.name: GEN0_STMP_CFG
1610694716.desc: Transfer status and update method for time stamp registers A and B

fields.name: CMPR0_A_UPMETHOD
fields.desc: Update method for PWM generator 0 time stamp A's active register. When all bits are set to 0: immediately, when bit0 is set to 1: TEZ, when bit1 is set to 1: TEP,when bit2 is set to 1: sync, when bit3 is set to 1: disable the update.

fields.name: CMPR0_B_UPMETHOD
fields.desc: Update method for PWM generator 0 time stamp B's active register. When all bits are set to 0: immediately, when bit0 is set to 1: TEZ, when bit1 is set to 1: TEP,when bit2 is set to 1: sync, when bit3 is set to 1: disable the update.

fields.name: CMPR0_A_SHDW_FULL
fields.desc: Set and reset by hardware. If set, PWM generator 0 time stamp A's shadow reg is filled and waiting to be transferred to A's active reg. If cleared, A's active reg has been updated with shadow register latest value

fields.name: CMPR0_B_SHDW_FULL
fields.desc: Set and reset by hardware. If set, PWM generator 0 time stamp B's shadow reg is filled and waiting to be transferred to B's active reg. If cleared, B's active reg has been updated with shadow register latest value

fields.name: CMPR0_A
fields.desc: PWM generator 0 time stamp A's shadow register

fields.name: CMPR0_B
fields.desc: PWM generator 0 time stamp B's shadow register

1610694728.name: GEN0_CFG0
1610694728.desc: Fault event T0 and T1 handling

fields.name: GEN0_CFG_UPMETHOD
fields.desc: Update method for PWM generator 0's active register of configuration. When all bits are set to 0: immediately, when bit0 is set to 1: TEZ, when bit1 is set to 1:TEP,when bit2 is set to 1:sync,when bit3 is set to 1:disable the update

fields.name: GEN0_T0_SEL
fields.desc: Source selection for PWM generator 0 event_t0, take effect immediately, 0: fault_event0, 1: fault_event1, 2: fault_event2, 3: sync_taken, 4: none

fields.name: GEN0_T1_SEL
fields.desc: Source selection for PWM generator 0 event_t1, take effect immediately, 0: fault_event0, 1: fault_event1, 2: fault_event2, 3: sync_taken, 4: none

fields.name: LOG_ENA
fields.desc: enable bus log. BIT0: hp-cpu, BIT1: lp-cpu, BIT2: DMA.823 don't support lp-cpu

fields.name: LOG_MODE
fields.desc: This field must be onehot. 4'b0001 : WR monitor, 4'b0010: WORD monitor, 4'b0100: HALFWORD monitor, 4'b1000: BYTE monitor.

fields.name: LOG_MEM_LOOP_ENABLE
fields.desc: Set 1 enable mem_loop, it will loop write at the range of MEM_START and MEM_END

fields.name: LOG_CHECK_DATA
fields.desc: The special check data, when write this special data, it will trigger logging.

fields.name: LOG_DATA_MASK
fields.desc: byte mask enable, BIT0 mask the first byte of MEM_MONITOR_LOG_CHECK_DATA, and BIT1 mask second byte, and so on.

fields.name: LOG_MIN
fields.desc: the min address of log range

fields.name: LOG_MAX
fields.desc: the max address of log range

fields.name: LOG_MEM_START
fields.desc: the start address of writing logging message

fields.name: LOG_MEM_END
fields.desc: the end address of writing logging message

fields.name: LOG_MEM_CURRENT_ADDR
fields.desc: means next writing address

fields.name: LOG_MEM_ADDR_UPDATE
fields.desc: Set 1 to updata MEM_MONITOR_LOG_MEM_CURRENT_ADDR, when set 1, MEM_MONITOR_LOG_MEM_CURRENT_ADDR will update to MEM_MONITOR_LOG_MEM_START

fields.name: LOG_MEM_FULL_FLAG
fields.desc: 1 means memory write loop at least one time at the range of MEM_START and MEM_END

fields.name: CLR_LOG_MEM_FULL_FLAG
fields.desc: Set 1 to clr MEM_MONITOR_LOG_MEM_FULL_FLAG

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: Set 1 to force on the clk of mem_monitor register

1610698752.name: RX_MODE_CFG
1610698752.desc: Parallel RX Sampling mode configuration register.

fields.name: RX_EXT_EN_SEL
fields.desc: Configures rx external enable signal selection from IO PAD.

fields.name: RX_SW_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable data sampling by software.

fields.name: RX_EXT_EN_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert the external enable signal.

fields.name: RX_PULSE_SUBMODE_SEL
fields.desc:
Configures the rxd pulse sampling submode. 
4'd0: positive pulse start(data bit included) &&  positive pulse end(data bit included)
4'd1: positive pulse start(data bit included) && positive pulse end (data bit excluded)
4'd2: positive pulse start(data bit excluded) && positive pulse end (data bit included)
4'd3: positive pulse start(data bit excluded) && positive pulse end (data bit excluded)
4'd4: positive pulse start(data bit included) && length end
4'd5: positive pulse start(data bit excluded) && length end

fields.name: RX_SMP_MODE_SEL
fields.desc:
Configures the rxd sampling mode. 
2'b00: external level enable mode
2'b01: external pulse enable mode  
2'b10: internal software enable mode

fields.name: RX_BITLEN
fields.desc: Configures expected byte number of received data.

fields.name: RX_DATA_ORDER_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert bit order of one byte sent from RX_FIFO to DMA.

fields.name: RX_BUS_WID_SEL
fields.desc:
Configures the rxd bus width. 
3'd0: bus width is 1.
3'd1: bus width is 2.
3'd2: bus width is 4.
3'd3: bus width is 8.

fields.name: RX_GATING_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the clock gating of output rx clock.

fields.name: RX_TIMEOUT_THRES
fields.desc: Configures threshold of timeout counter.

fields.name: RX_TIMEOUT_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable timeout function to generate error eof.

fields.name: RX_EOF_GEN_SEL
fields.desc: Configures the DMA eof generated mechanism. 1'b0: eof generated by data byte length. 1'b1: eof generated by external enable signal.

fields.name: RX_START
fields.desc: Set this bit to start rx data sampling.

fields.name: TX_BITLEN
fields.desc: Configures expected byte number of sent data.

fields.name: TX_DATA_ORDER_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert bit order of one byte sent from TX_FIFO to IO data.

fields.name: TX_BUS_WID_SEL
fields.desc:
Configures the txd bus width. 
3'd0: bus width is 1.
3'd1: bus width is 2.
3'd2: bus width is 4.
3'd3: bus width is 8.

fields.name: TX_START
fields.desc: Set this bit to start tx data transmit.

fields.name: TX_IDLE_VALUE
fields.desc: Configures bus value of transmitter in IDLE state.

fields.name: TX_GATING_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the clock gating of output tx clock.

fields.name: TX_VALID_OUTPUT_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the output of tx data valid signal.

fields.name: TX_FIFO_SRST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset async fifo in tx module.

fields.name: RX_FIFO_SRST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset async fifo in rx module.

fields.name: RX_REG_UPDATE
fields.desc: Set this bit to update rx register configuration.

fields.name: TX_READY
fields.desc: Represents the status that tx is ready to transmit.

fields.desc: Set this bit to enable RX_FIFO_WOVF_INT.

fields.name: TX_EOF_INT_ENA

fields.desc: The masked interrupt status of RX_FIFO_WOVF_INT.

fields.name: TX_EOF_INT_ST

fields.name: CH0_NEG_MODE
fields.desc:
This register sets the behavior when the signal input of channel 0 detects a negative edge.

1: Increase the counter.2: Decrease the counter.0, 3: No effect on counter

fields.name: CH0_POS_MODE
fields.desc:
This register sets the behavior when the signal input of channel 0 detects a positive edge.

1: Increase the counter.2: Decrease the counter.0, 3: No effect on counter

fields.name: CH0_HCTRL_MODE
fields.desc:
This register configures how the CH%s_POS_MODE/CH%s_NEG_MODE settings will be modified when the control signal is high.

0: No modification.1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase).2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

fields.name: CH0_LCTRL_MODE
fields.desc:
This register configures how the CH%s_POS_MODE/CH%s_NEG_MODE settings will be modified when the control signal is low.

0: No modification.1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase).2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

fields.name: CH1_NEG_MODE
fields.desc:
This register sets the behavior when the signal input of channel 1 detects a negative edge.

1: Increment the counter.2: Decrement the counter.0, 3: No effect on counter

fields.name: CH1_POS_MODE
fields.desc:
This register sets the behavior when the signal input of channel 1 detects a positive edge.

1: Increment the counter.2: Decrement the counter.0, 3: No effect on counter

fields.name: CH1_HCTRL_MODE
fields.desc:
This register configures how the CH%s_POS_MODE/CH%s_NEG_MODE settings will be modified when the control signal is high.

0: No modification.1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase).2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

fields.name: CH1_LCTRL_MODE
fields.desc:
This register configures how the CH%s_POS_MODE/CH%s_NEG_MODE settings will be modified when the control signal is low.

0: No modification.1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase).2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

fields.name: I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: Integral I2S TX clock divider value. f_I2S_CLK = f_I2S_CLK_S/(N+b/a). There will be (a-b) * n-div and b * (n+1)-div.  So the average combination will be:  for b <= a/2, z * [x * n-div + (n+1)-div] + y * n-div. For b > a/2, z * [n-div + x * (n+1)-div] + y * (n+1)-div.

fields.desc: Select I2S Tx module source clock. 0: XTAL clock. 1: APLL. 2: CLK160. 3: I2S_MCLK_in.

fields.name: I2S_TX_CLKM_EN
fields.desc: Set 1 to enable i2s_tx function clock

fields.name: I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_Z
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_Z is b. For b > a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_Z is (a-b).

fields.name: I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_Y
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_Y is (a%b) . For b > a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_Y is (a%(a-b)).

fields.name: I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_X
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_X is (a/b) - 1. For b > a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_X is (a/(a-b)) - 1.

fields.name: I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_YN1
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_YN1 is 0 . For b > a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_YN1 is 1.

fields.name: I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_NUM

fields.desc: clk_hproot is div1 of low-speed clock-source if clck-source is a low-speed clock-source such as XTAL/FOSC.

fields.desc: clk_hproot is div3 of SPLL if the clock-source is high-speed clock SPLL.

fields.desc: This field is used to select clock source. 0: XTAL, 1: SPLL, 2: FOSC, 3: reserved.

fields.desc: This field indicates the frequency(MHz) of XTAL.

fields.name: PLL_FREQ_SEL
fields.desc: Reserved. This filed has been replaced by PCR_CPU_DIV_NUM

fields.name: CPU_WAIT_MODE_FORCE_ON
fields.desc: Set 1 to force cpu_waiti_clk enable.

fields.name: CPU_WAITI_DELAY_NUM
fields.desc: This field used to set delay cycle when cpu enter waiti mode, after delay waiti_clk will close

fields.name: CPU_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: Set this field to generate clk_cpu drived by clk_hproot. The clk_cpu is div1(default)/div2/div4 of clk_hproot. This field is only avaliable for low-speed clock-source such as XTAL/FOSC, and should be used together with PCR_AHB_DIV_NUM.

fields.name: AHB_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: Set this field to generate clk_ahb drived by clk_hproot. The clk_ahb is div1(default)/div2/div4/div8 of clk_hproot. This field is only avaliable for low-speed clock-source such as XTAL/FOSC, and should be used together with PCR_CPU_DIV_NUM.

fields.name: APB_DECREASE_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: If this field's value is grater than PCR_APB_DIV_NUM, the clk_apb will be automatically down to clk_apb_decrease only when no access is on apb-bus, and will recover to the previous frequency when a new access appears on apb-bus. Set as one within (0,1,3) to set clk_apb_decrease as div1/div2/div4(default) of clk_ahb. Note that enable this function will reduce performance. Users can set this field as zero to disable the auto-decrease-apb-freq function. By default, this function is disable.

fields.name: APB_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: Set as one within (0,1,3) to generate clk_apb drived by clk_ahb. The clk_apb is div1(default)/div2/div4 of clk_ahb.

fields.name: FOSC_FREQ
fields.desc: This field indicates the frequency(MHz) of FOSC.

fields.name: PLL_FREQ
fields.desc: This field indicates the frequency(MHz) of SPLL.

fields.name: PLL_240M_CLK_EN
fields.desc: This field is used to open 96 MHz clock (SPLL) drived from SPLL. 0: close, 1: open(default). Only avaliable when high-speed clock-source SPLL is active.

fields.name: PLL_160M_CLK_EN
fields.desc: This field is used to open 64 MHz clock (div3 of SPLL) drived from SPLL. 0: close, 1: open(default). Only avaliable when high-speed clock-source SPLL is active.

fields.name: PLL_120M_CLK_EN
fields.desc: This field is used to open 48 MHz clock (div4 of SPLL) drived from SPLL. 0: close, 1: open(default). Only avaliable when high-speed clock-source SPLL is active.

fields.name: PLL_80M_CLK_EN
fields.desc: This field is used to open 32 MHz clock (div6  of SPLL) drived from SPLL. 0: close, 1: open(default). Only avaliable when high-speed clock-source SPLL is active.

fields.name: PLL_48M_CLK_EN
fields.desc: This field is used to open 16 MHz clock (div10 of SPLL) drived from SPLL. 0: close, 1: open(default). Only avaliable when high-speed clock-source SPLL is active.

fields.name: PLL_40M_CLK_EN
fields.desc: This field is used to open 8 MHz clock (div12 of SPLL) drived from SPLL. 0: close, 1: open(default). Only avaliable when high-speed clock-source SPLL is active.

fields.desc: Set this bit to reset read ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing transmitter.

fields.name: APB_MEM_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset W/R ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing apb fifo.

fields.name: TX_CONTI_MODE
fields.desc: Set this bit to restart transmission  from the first data to the last data in CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: MEM_TX_WRAP_EN
fields.desc: This is the channel %s enable bit for wraparound mode: it will resume sending at the start when the data to be sent is more than its memory size.

fields.name: IDLE_OUT_LV
fields.desc: This bit configures the level of output signal in CHANNEL%s when the latter is in IDLE state.

fields.name: IDLE_OUT_EN
fields.desc: This is the output enable-control bit for CHANNEL%s in IDLE state.

fields.name: TX_STOP
fields.desc: Set this bit to stop the transmitter of CHANNEL%s sending data out.

fields.name: DIV_CNT
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the divider for clock of CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: MEM_SIZE
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the maximum size of memory allocated to CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: CARRIER_EFF_EN
fields.desc: 1: Add carrier modulation on the output signal only at the send data state for CHANNEL%s. 0: Add carrier modulation on the output signal at all state for CHANNEL%s. Only valid when RMT_CARRIER_EN_CH%s is 1.

fields.name: CARRIER_EN
fields.desc: This is the carrier modulation enable-control bit for CHANNEL%s. 1: Add carrier modulation in the output signal. 0: No carrier modulation in sig_out.

fields.name: CARRIER_OUT_LV
fields.desc:
This bit is used to configure the position of carrier wave for CHANNEL%s.

1'h0: add carrier wave on low level.

1'h1: add carrier wave on high level.

fields.name: AFIFO_RST
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: CONF_UPDATE
fields.desc: synchronization bit for CHANNEL%s

fields.name: DIV_CNT
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the divider for clock of CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: IDLE_THRES
fields.desc: When no edge is detected on the input signal and continuous clock cycles is longer than this register value, received process is finished.

fields.name: MEM_SIZE
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the maximum size of memory allocated to CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: CARRIER_EN
fields.desc: This is the carrier modulation enable-control bit for CHANNEL%s. 1: Add carrier modulation in the output signal. 0: No carrier modulation in sig_out.

fields.name: CARRIER_OUT_LV
fields.desc:
This bit is used to configure the position of carrier wave for CHANNEL%s.

1'h0: add carrier wave on low level.

1'h1: add carrier wave on high level.

fields.name: RX_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable receiver to receive data on CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: MEM_WR_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset write ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing receiver.

fields.name: APB_MEM_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset W/R ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing apb fifo.

fields.name: MEM_OWNER
fields.desc:
This register marks the ownership of CHANNEL%s's ram block.

1'h1: Receiver is using the ram. 

1'h0: APB bus is using the ram.

fields.name: RX_FILTER_EN
fields.desc: This is the receive filter's enable bit for CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: RX_FILTER_THRES
fields.desc: Ignores the input pulse when its width is smaller than this register value in APB clock periods (in receive mode).

fields.name: MEM_RX_WRAP_EN
fields.desc: This is the channel %s enable bit for wraparound mode: it will resume receiving at the start when the data to be received is more than its memory size.

fields.name: AFIFO_RST
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: CONF_UPDATE
fields.desc: synchronization bit for CHANNEL%s

fields.name: MEM_RADDR_EX
fields.desc: This register records the memory address offset when transmitter of CHANNEL%s is using the RAM.

fields.name: APB_MEM_WADDR
fields.desc: This register records the memory address offset when writes RAM over APB bus.

fields.name: APB_MEM_RD_ERR
fields.desc: This status bit will be set if the offset address out of memory size when reading via APB bus.

fields.name: MEM_EMPTY
fields.desc: This status bit will be set when the data to be set is more than memory size and the wraparound mode is disabled.

fields.name: APB_MEM_WR_ERR
fields.desc: This status bit will be set if the offset address out of memory size when writes via APB bus.

fields.name: APB_MEM_RADDR
fields.desc: This register records the memory address offset when reading RAM over APB bus.

fields.name: MEM_WADDR_EX
fields.desc: This register records the memory address offset when receiver of CHANNEL%s is using the RAM.

fields.desc: This register records the memory address offset when reads RAM over APB bus.

fields.name: MEM_OWNER_ERR
fields.desc: This status bit will be set when the ownership of memory block is wrong.

fields.name: MEM_FULL
fields.desc: This status bit will be set if the receiver receives more data than the memory size.

fields.name: APB_MEM_RD_ERR
fields.desc: This status bit will be set if the offset address out of memory size when reads via APB bus.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: clock enable

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: date

fields.name: SPI_MEM_MST_ST
fields.desc: The current status of SPI0 master FSM: spi0_mst_st. 0: idle state, 1:SPI0_GRANT , 2: program/erase suspend state, 3: SPI0 read data state, 4: wait cache/EDMA sent data is stored in SPI0 TX FIFO, 5: SPI0 write data state.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SLV_ST
fields.desc: The current status of SPI0 slave FSM: mspi_st. 0: idle state, 1: preparation state, 2: send command state, 3: send address state, 4: wait state, 5: read data state, 6:write data state, 7: done state, 8: read data end state.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR
fields.desc: SPI0 USR_CMD start bit, only used when SPI_MEM_AXI_REQ_EN is cleared.  An operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WDUMMY_DQS_ALWAYS_OUT
fields.desc: In the dummy phase of an MSPI write data transfer when accesses to flash, the level of SPI_DQS is output by the MSPI controller.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WDUMMY_ALWAYS_OUT
fields.desc: In the dummy phase of an MSPI write data transfer when accesses to flash, the level of SPI_IO[7:0] is output by the MSPI controller.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDUMMY_RIN
fields.desc: In an MSPI read data transfer when accesses to flash, the level of SPI_IO[7:0] is output by the MSPI controller in the first half part of dummy phase. It is used to mask invalid SPI_DQS in the half part of dummy phase.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDUMMY_WOUT
fields.desc: In an MSPI write data transfer when accesses to flash, the level of SPI_IO[7:0] is output by the MSPI controller in the second half part of dummy phase. It is used to pre-drive flash.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDOUT_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8 signals during write-data phase 1:enable 0: disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDIN_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8 signals during read-data phase 1:enable 0: disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FADDR_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8 signals during address phase 1:enable 0: disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FCMD_QUAD
fields.desc: Apply 4 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FCMD_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FASTRD_MODE
fields.desc: This bit enable the bits: SPI_MEM_FREAD_QIO, SPI_MEM_FREAD_DIO, SPI_MEM_FREAD_QOUT and SPI_MEM_FREAD_DOUT. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_DUAL
fields.desc: In the read operations, read-data phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_Q_POL
fields.desc: The bit is used to set MISO line polarity, 1: high 0, low

fields.name: SPI_MEM_D_POL
fields.desc: The bit is used to set MOSI line polarity, 1: high 0, low

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_QUAD
fields.desc: In the read operations read-data phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WP
fields.desc: Write protect signal output when SPI is idle.  1: output high, 0: output low.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_DIO
fields.desc: In the read operations address phase and read-data phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_QIO
fields.desc: In the read operations address phase and read-data phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_DQS_IE_ALWAYS_ON
fields.desc: When accesses to flash, 1: the IE signals of pads connected to SPI_DQS are always 1. 0: Others.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_DATA_IE_ALWAYS_ON
fields.desc: When accesses to flash, 1: the IE signals of pads connected to SPI_IO[7:0] are always 1. 0: Others.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CLK_MODE
fields.desc: SPI clock mode bits. 0: SPI clock is off when CS inactive 1: SPI clock is delayed one cycle after CS inactive 2: SPI clock is delayed two cycles after CS inactive 3: SPI clock is alwasy on.

fields.name: SPI_AR_SIZE0_1_SUPPORT_EN
fields.desc: 1: MSPI supports ARSIZE 0~3. When ARSIZE =0~2, MSPI read address is 4*n and reply the real AXI read data back. 0: When ARSIZE 0~1, MSPI reply SLV_ERR.

fields.name: SPI_AW_SIZE0_1_SUPPORT_EN
fields.desc: 1: MSPI supports AWSIZE 0~3. 0: When AWSIZE 0~1, MSPI reply SLV_ERR.

fields.name: SPI_AXI_RDATA_BACK_FAST
fields.desc: 1: Reply AXI read data to AXI bus when one AXI read beat data is available. 0: Reply AXI read data to AXI bus when all the read data is available.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_RRESP_ECC_ERR_EN
fields.desc: 1: RRESP is SLV_ERR when there is a ECC error in AXI read data. 0: RRESP is OKAY when there is a ECC error in AXI read data. The ECC error information is recorded in SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_ADDR_REG.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AR_SPLICE_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable AXI Read Splice-transfer.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AW_SPLICE_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable AXI Write Splice-transfer.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_RAM0_EN
fields.desc: When SPI_MEM_DUAL_RAM_EN is 0 and SPI_MEM_RAM0_EN is 1, only EXT_RAM0 will be accessed. When SPI_MEM_DUAL_RAM_EN is 0 and SPI_MEM_RAM0_EN is 0, only EXT_RAM1 will be accessed. When SPI_MEM_DUAL_RAM_EN is 1,  EXT_RAM0 and EXT_RAM1 will be accessed at the same time.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_DUAL_RAM_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable DUAL-RAM mode, EXT_RAM0 and EXT_RAM1 will be accessed at the same time.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FAST_WRITE_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to write data faster, do not wait write data has been stored in tx_bus_fifo_l2. It will wait 4*T_clk_ctrl to insure the write data has been stored in  tx_bus_fifo_l2.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_RXFIFO_RST
fields.desc: The synchronous reset signal for SPI0 RX AFIFO and all the AES_MSPI SYNC FIFO to receive signals from AXI.  Set this bit to reset these FIFO.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_TXFIFO_RST
fields.desc: The synchronous reset signal for SPI0 TX AFIFO and all the AES_MSPI SYNC FIFO to send signals to AXI. Set this bit to reset these FIFO.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CS_SETUP_TIME
fields.desc: (cycles-1) of prepare phase by SPI Bus clock, this bits are combined with SPI_MEM_CS_SETUP bit.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_TIME
fields.desc: SPI CS signal is delayed to inactive by SPI bus clock, this bits are combined with SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD bit.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_CS_HOLD_TIME
fields.desc: SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_TIME + SPI_MEM_ECC_CS_HOLD_TIME is the SPI0 CS hold cycle in ECC mode when accessed flash.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_SKIP_PAGE_CORNER
fields.desc: 1: SPI0 and SPI1 skip page corner when accesses flash. 0: Not skip page corner when accesses flash.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_16TO18_BYTE_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable SPI0 and SPI1 ECC 16 bytes data with 2 ECC bytes mode when accesses flash.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SPLIT_TRANS_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable SPI0 split one AXI read flash transfer into two SPI transfers when one transfer will cross flash or EXT_RAM page corner, valid no matter whether there is an ECC region or not.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY
fields.desc: These bits are used to set the minimum CS high time tSHSL between SPI burst transfer when accesses to flash. tSHSL is (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY[5:0] + 1) MSPI core clock cycles.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SYNC_RESET
fields.desc: The spi0_mst_st and spi0_slv_st will be reset.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_L
fields.desc: In the master mode it must be equal to spi_mem_clkcnt_N.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_H
fields.desc: In the master mode it must be floor((spi_mem_clkcnt_N+1)/2-1).

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_N
fields.desc: In the master mode it is the divider of spi_mem_clk. So spi_mem_clk frequency is system/(spi_mem_clkcnt_N+1)

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CLK_EQU_SYSCLK
fields.desc: 1: 1-division mode, the frequency of SPI bus clock equals to that of MSPI module clock.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD
fields.desc: spi cs keep low when spi is in  done  phase. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CS_SETUP
fields.desc: spi cs is enable when spi is in  prepare  phase. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CK_OUT_EDGE
fields.desc: The bit combined with SPI_MEM_CK_IDLE_EDGE bit to control SPI clock mode 0~3.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_DUMMY_IDLE
fields.desc: spi clock is disable in dummy phase when the bit is enable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_DUMMY
fields.desc: This bit enable the dummy phase of an operation.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: The length in spi_mem_clk cycles of dummy phase. The register value shall be (cycle_num-1).

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_DBYTELEN
fields.desc: SPI0 USR_CMD read or write data byte length -1

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_ADDR_BITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of address phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_COMMAND_VALUE
fields.desc: The value of  command.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_COMMAND_BITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of command phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1)

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WB_MODE
fields.desc: Mode bits in the flash fast read mode  it is combined with spi_mem_fastrd_mode bit.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FSUB_PIN
fields.desc: For SPI0,  flash is connected to SUBPINs.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SSUB_PIN
fields.desc: For SPI0,  sram is connected to SUBPINs.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CK_IDLE_EDGE
fields.desc: 1: SPI_CLK line is high when idle     0: spi clk line is low when idle

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CS_KEEP_ACTIVE
fields.desc: SPI_CS line keep low when the bit is set.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AXI_REQ_EN
fields.desc: For SPI0, AXI master access enable, 1: enable, 0:disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_USR_ADDR_4BYTE
fields.desc: For SPI0,  cache  read flash with 4 bytes address, 1: enable, 0:disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_FLASH_USR_CMD
fields.desc: For SPI0,  cache  read flash for user define command, 1: enable, 0:disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDIN_DUAL
fields.desc: For SPI0 flash, din phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_dio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDOUT_DUAL
fields.desc: For SPI0 flash, dout phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_dio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FADDR_DUAL
fields.desc: For SPI0 flash, address phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_dio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDIN_QUAD
fields.desc: For SPI0 flash, din phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_qio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDOUT_QUAD
fields.desc: For SPI0 flash, dout phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_qio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FADDR_QUAD
fields.desc: For SPI0 flash, address phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_qio.

fields.name: SPI_SAME_AW_AR_ADDR_CHK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to check AXI read/write the same address region.

fields.name: SPI_CLOSE_AXI_INF_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to close AXI read/write transfer to MSPI, which means that only SLV_ERR will be replied to BRESP/RRESP.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_USR_SADDR_4BYTE
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, cache read flash with 4 bytes command, 1: enable, 0:disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_SRAM_DIO
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, spi dual I/O mode enable, 1: enable, 0:disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_SRAM_QIO
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, spi quad I/O mode enable, 1: enable, 0:disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_WR_SRAM_DUMMY
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, it is the enable bit of dummy phase for write operations.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_RD_SRAM_DUMMY
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, it is the enable bit of dummy phase for read operations.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_SRAM_USR_RCMD
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode cache read external RAM for user define command.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SRAM_RDUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, it is the length in bits of read dummy phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SRAM_ADDR_BITLEN
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, it is the length in bits of address phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_SRAM_USR_WCMD
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode cache write sram for user define command

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SRAM_OCT
fields.desc: reserved

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SRAM_WDUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, it is the length in bits of write dummy phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

1610620996.name: SPI_MEM_SRAM_CMD
1610620996.desc: SPI0 external RAM mode control register

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SCLK_MODE
fields.desc: SPI clock mode bits. 0: SPI clock is off when CS inactive 1: SPI clock is delayed one cycle after CS inactive 2: SPI clock is delayed two cycles after CS inactive 3: SPI clock is always on.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SWB_MODE
fields.desc: Mode bits in the external RAM fast read mode  it is combined with spi_mem_fastrd_mode bit.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDIN_DUAL
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , din phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_usr_sram_dio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDOUT_DUAL
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , dout phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_usr_sram_dio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SADDR_DUAL
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , address phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_usr_sram_dio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDIN_QUAD
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , din phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_usr_sram_qio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDOUT_QUAD
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , dout phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_usr_sram_qio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SADDR_QUAD
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , address phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_usr_sram_qio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SCMD_QUAD
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , cmd phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_usr_sram_qio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDIN_OCT
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , din phase apply 8 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDOUT_OCT
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , dout phase apply 8 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SADDR_OCT
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , address phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SCMD_OCT
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , cmd phase apply 8 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDUMMY_RIN
fields.desc: In the dummy phase of a MSPI read data transfer when accesses to external RAM, the signal level of SPI bus is output by the MSPI controller.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDUMMY_WOUT
fields.desc: In the dummy phase of a MSPI write data transfer when accesses to external RAM, the signal level of SPI bus is output by the MSPI controller.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_WDUMMY_DQS_ALWAYS_OUT
fields.desc: In the dummy phase of an MSPI write data transfer when accesses to external RAM, the level of SPI_DQS is output by the MSPI controller.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_WDUMMY_ALWAYS_OUT
fields.desc: In the dummy phase of an MSPI write data transfer when accesses to external RAM, the level of SPI_IO[7:0] is output by the MSPI controller.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_DQS_IE_ALWAYS_ON
fields.desc: When accesses to external RAM, 1: the IE signals of pads connected to SPI_DQS are always 1. 0: Others.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_DATA_IE_ALWAYS_ON
fields.desc: When accesses to external RAM, 1: the IE signals of pads connected to SPI_IO[7:0] are always 1. 0: Others.

1610621000.name: SPI_MEM_SRAM_DRD_CMD
1610621000.desc: SPI0 external RAM DDR read command control register

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_SRAM_USR_RD_CMD_VALUE
fields.desc: For SPI0,When cache mode is enable it is the read command value of command phase for sram.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_SRAM_USR_RD_CMD_BITLEN
fields.desc: For SPI0,When cache mode is enable it is the length in bits of command phase for sram. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

1610621004.name: SPI_MEM_SRAM_DWR_CMD
1610621004.desc: SPI0 external RAM DDR write command control register

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_SRAM_USR_WR_CMD_VALUE
fields.desc: For SPI0,When cache mode is enable it is the write command value of command phase for sram.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_SRAM_USR_WR_CMD_BITLEN
fields.desc: For SPI0,When cache mode is enable it is the in bits of command phase  for sram. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

1610621008.name: SPI_MEM_SRAM_CLK
1610621008.desc: SPI0 external RAM clock control register

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SCLKCNT_L
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM  interface, it must be equal to spi_mem_clkcnt_N.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SCLKCNT_H
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM  interface, it must be floor((spi_mem_clkcnt_N+1)/2-1).

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SCLKCNT_N
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM  interface, it is the divider of spi_mem_clk. So spi_mem_clk frequency is system/(spi_mem_clkcnt_N+1)

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SCLK_EQU_SYSCLK
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM  interface, 1: spi_mem_clk is eqaul to system 0: spi_mem_clk is divided from system clock.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_LOCK_DELAY_TIME
fields.desc: The lock delay time of SPI0/1 arbiter by spi0_slv_st, after PER is sent by SPI1.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PMS_REJECT_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_PMS_REJECT_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AXI_RADDR_ERR_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_AXI_RADDR_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AXI_WR_FLASH_ERR_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_AXI_WR_FALSH_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AXI_WADDR_ERR_INT__ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_AXI_WADDR_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT_CLR
fields.desc: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT_CLR
fields.desc: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_CLR
fields.desc: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when spi0_slv_st is changed from non idle state to idle state. It means that SPI_CS raises high. 0: Others

fields.name: SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when spi0_mst_st is changed from non idle state to idle state. 0: Others.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT interrupt. When SPI_FMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN is set and  SPI_SMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN is cleared, this bit is triggered when the error times of SPI0/1 ECC read flash are equal or bigger than SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_NUM. When SPI_FMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN is cleared and  SPI_SMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN is set, this bit is triggered when the error times of SPI0/1 ECC read external RAM are equal or bigger than SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_NUM. When SPI_FMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN and  SPI_SMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN are set, this bit is triggered when the total error times of SPI0/1 ECC read external RAM and flash are equal or bigger than SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_NUM. When SPI_FMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN and  SPI_SMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN are cleared, this bit will not be triggered.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PMS_REJECT_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_PMS_REJECT_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when SPI1 access is rejected. 0: Others.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AXI_RADDR_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_AXI_RADDR_ERR_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when AXI read address is invalid by compared to MMU configuration. 0: Others.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AXI_WR_FLASH_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_AXI_WR_FALSH_ERR_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when AXI write flash request is received. 0: Others.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AXI_WADDR_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_AXI_WADDR_ERR_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when AXI write address is invalid by compared to MMU configuration. 0: Others.

1610621140.name: SPI_MEM_DDR
1610621140.desc: SPI0 flash DDR mode control register

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_EN
fields.desc: 1: in DDR mode,  0 in SDR mode

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_VAR_DUMMY
fields.desc: Set the bit to enable variable dummy cycle in spi DDR mode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_RDAT_SWP
fields.desc: Set the bit to reorder rx data of the word in spi DDR mode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_WDAT_SWP
fields.desc: Set the bit to reorder tx data of the word in spi DDR mode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_CMD_DIS
fields.desc: the bit is used to disable dual edge in command phase when DDR mode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_OUTMINBYTELEN
fields.desc: It is the minimum output data length in the panda device.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_TX_DDR_MSK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to mask the first or the last byte in SPI0 ECC DDR write mode, when accesses to flash.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_RX_DDR_MSK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to mask the first or the last byte in SPI0 ECC DDR read mode, when accesses to flash.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_USR_DDR_DQS_THD
fields.desc: The delay number of data strobe which from memory based on SPI clock.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_DQS_LOOP
fields.desc: 1: Do not need the input of SPI_DQS signal, SPI0 starts to receive data when spi0_slv_st is in SPI_MEM_DIN state. It is used when there is no SPI_DQS signal or SPI_DQS signal is not stable. 0: SPI0 starts to store data at the positive and negative edge of SPI_DQS.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_CLK_DIFF_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the differential SPI_CLK#.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DQS_CA_IN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the input of SPI_DQS signal in SPI phases of CMD and ADDR.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_HYPERBUS_DUMMY_2X
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the vary dummy function in SPI HyperBus mode, when SPI0 accesses flash or SPI1 accesses flash or sram.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_CLK_DIFF_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert SPI_DIFF when accesses to flash. .

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_OCTA_RAM_ADDR
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable octa_ram address out when accesses to flash, which means ADDR_OUT[31:0] = {spi_usr_addr_value[25:4], 6'd0, spi_usr_addr_value[3:1], 1'b0}.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_HYPERBUS_CA
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable HyperRAM address out when accesses to flash, which means ADDR_OUT[31:0] = {spi_usr_addr_value[19:4], 13'd0, spi_usr_addr_value[3:1]}.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_OUTMINBYTELEN

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_TX_DDR_MSK_EN

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_RX_DDR_MSK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to mask the first or the last byte in SPI0 ECC DDR read mode, when accesses to external RAM.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_USR_DDR_DQS_THD
fields.desc: The delay number of data strobe which from memory based on SPI clock.

fields.desc: 1: Do not need the input of SPI_DQS signal, SPI0 starts to receive data when spi0_slv_st is in SPI_MEM_DIN state. It is used when there is no SPI_DQS signal or SPI_DQS signal is not stable. 0: SPI0 starts to store data at the positive and negative edge of SPI_DQS.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_CLK_DIFF_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the differential SPI_CLK#.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_DQS_CA_IN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the input of SPI_DQS signal in SPI phases of CMD and ADDR.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_HYPERBUS_DUMMY_2X
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the vary dummy function in SPI HyperBus mode, when SPI0 accesses flash or SPI1 accesses flash or sram.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_CLK_DIFF_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert SPI_DIFF when accesses to external RAM. .

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_OCTA_RAM_ADDR
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable octa_ram address out when accesses to external RAM, which means ADDR_OUT[31:0] = {spi_usr_addr_value[25:4], 6'd0, spi_usr_addr_value[3:1], 1'b0}.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_HYPERBUS_CA
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable HyperRAM address out when accesses to external RAM, which means ADDR_OUT[31:0] = {spi_usr_addr_value[19:4], 13'd0, spi_usr_addr_value[3:1]}.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_PMS_RD_ATTR

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_PMS_WR_ATTR

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_PMS_ECC

fields.desc: SPI1 flash ACE section %s address region is (SPI_FMEM_PMS%s_ADDR_S, SPI_FMEM_PMS%s_ADDR_S + SPI_FMEM_PMS%s_SIZE)

fields.name: SPI_MEM_REJECT_ADDR
fields.desc: This bits show the first SPI1 access error address. It is cleared by when  SPI_MEM_PMS_REJECT_INT_CLR bit is set.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PM_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable SPI0/1 transfer permission control function.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PMS_LD
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 write access error. 0: No write access error. It is cleared by when  SPI_MEM_PMS_REJECT_INT_CLR bit is set.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PMS_ST
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 read access error. 0: No read access error. It is cleared by when  SPI_MEM_PMS_REJECT_INT_CLR bit is set.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PMS_MULTI_HIT
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 access is rejected because of address miss. 0: No address miss error. It is cleared by when  SPI_MEM_PMS_REJECT_INT_CLR bit is set.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PMS_IVD
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 access is rejected because of address multi-hit. 0: No address multi-hit error. It is cleared by when  SPI_MEM_PMS_REJECT_INT_CLR bit is set.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_NUM
fields.desc: Set the error times of MSPI ECC read to generate MSPI SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to calculate the error times of MSPI ECC read when accesses to flash.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_PAGE_SIZE
fields.desc: Set the page size of the flash accessed by MSPI. 0: 256 bytes. 1: 512 bytes. 2: 1024 bytes. 3: 2048 bytes.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_ECC_ADDR_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable MSPI ECC address conversion, no matter MSPI accesses to the ECC region or non-ECC region of flash. If there is no ECC region in flash, this bit should be 0. Otherwise, this bit should be 1.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_ECC_ADDR_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable ECC address convert in SPI0/1 USR_CMD transfer.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_CONTINUE_RECORD_ERR_EN
fields.desc: 1: The error information in SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_BITS and SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_ADDR is updated when there is an ECC error. 0: SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_BITS and SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_ADDR record the first ECC error information.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_BITS
fields.desc: Records the first ECC error bit number in the 16 bytes(From 0~127, corresponding to byte 0 bit 0 to byte 15 bit 7)

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_ADDR
fields.desc: This bits show the first MSPI ECC error address. It is cleared by when  SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_CLR bit is set.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_CNT
fields.desc: This bits show the error times of MSPI ECC read. It is cleared by when  SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_CLR bit is set.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AXI_ERR_ADDR
fields.desc: This bits show the first AXI write/read invalid error or AXI write flash error address. It is cleared by when SPI_MEM_AXI_WADDR_ERR_INT_CLR, SPI_MEM_AXI_WR_FLASH_ERR_IN_CLR or SPI_MEM_AXI_RADDR_ERR_IN_CLR bit is set.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ALL_FIFO_EMPTY
fields.desc: The empty status of all AFIFO and SYNC_FIFO in MSPI module. 1: All AXI transfers and SPI0 transfers are done. 0: Others.

fields.name: SPI_RDATA_AFIFO_REMPTY
fields.desc: 1: RDATA_AFIFO is empty. 0: At least one AXI read transfer is pending.

fields.name: SPI_RADDR_AFIFO_REMPTY
fields.desc: 1: AXI_RADDR_CTL_AFIFO is empty. 0: At least one AXI read transfer is pending.

fields.name: SPI_WDATA_AFIFO_REMPTY
fields.desc: 1: WDATA_AFIFO is empty. 0: At least one AXI write transfer is pending.

fields.name: SPI_WBLEN_AFIFO_REMPTY
fields.desc: 1: WBLEN_AFIFO is empty. 0: At least one AXI write transfer is pending.

fields.name: SPI_ALL_AXI_TRANS_AFIFO_EMPTY
fields.desc: This bit is set when WADDR_AFIFO, WBLEN_AFIFO, WDATA_AFIFO, AXI_RADDR_CTL_AFIFO and RDATA_AFIFO are empty and spi0_mst_st is IDLE.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to calculate the error times of MSPI ECC read when accesses to external RAM.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_PAGE_SIZE
fields.desc: Set the page size of the external RAM accessed by MSPI. 0: 256 bytes. 1: 512 bytes. 2: 1024 bytes. 3: 2048 bytes.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_ECC_ADDR_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable MSPI ECC address conversion, no matter MSPI accesses to the ECC region or non-ECC region of external RAM. If there is no ECC region in external RAM, this bit should be 0. Otherwise, this bit should be 1.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_TIMING_CLK_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable timing adjust clock for all reading operations.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_TIMING_CALI
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable timing auto-calibration for all reading operations.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_EXTRA_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: add extra dummy spi clock cycle length for spi clock calibration.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_DLL_TIMING_CALI
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable DLL for timing calibration in DDR mode when accessed to flash.

fields.name: UPDATE
fields.desc: Set this bit to update delay mode, delay num and extra dummy in MSPI.
